-Everyone, listen!
-No, that's not true.

35
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:29,399
-My little brother tried to kill me!
-That's not true.

36
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:34,487
No, Sang-tae. That's not true.

37
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:41,077
CHAPTER 10
THE GIRL WHO CRIED WOLF

38
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:45,915
UNDER SEDATION
DO NOT DISTURB

39
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,376
Did he fall asleep?

40
00:02:48,877 --> 00:02:49,711
Yes.

41
00:02:56,801 --> 00:02:59,220
We gave him sedatives, and he fell asleep.

42
00:03:00,597 --> 00:03:02,348
Why don't you let him stay here
for a while?

43
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:04,851
I'm not saying he should be hospitalized.

44
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:07,395
We'll just temporarily
take care of him here.

45
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:10,982
Okay.

46
00:03:17,155 --> 00:03:18,823
He'll be asleep for a while.

47
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:23,912
You should go outside and get some air.

48
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:23,471
Hey, where are you going?

49
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:27,684
How far are you going to walk?

50
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:31,854
My feet hurt.

51
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:34,857
Gang-tae!

52
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:41,197
I told you not to turn your back on me!

53
00:04:56,963 --> 00:04:57,964
It's your fault

54
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:01,092
for having such a broad back.

55
00:05:04,053 --> 00:05:04,971
Aren't you hungry?

56
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:08,766
There's a delicious udon restaurant

57
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:10,810
-two train stops away from here.
-Ko Mun-yeong.

58
00:05:13,938 --> 00:05:15,231
Stop following me.

59
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:25,992
But we go hand in hand.
We should be together.

60
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:30,455
Go home.

61
00:05:32,248 --> 00:05:33,499
I need to be with my brother.

62
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:38,463
You did nothing wrong.

63
00:05:41,632 --> 00:05:43,301
Your brother just got unlucky

64
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:45,053
and fell into the river that day.

65
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:49,932
Gang-tae! Help!

66
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:51,392
Gang-tae!

67
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:55,146
You were a coward,
but you weren't malicious.

68
00:05:58,232 --> 00:05:59,442
You ran away, but in the end,

69
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:02,111
you came back and saved your brother.

70
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:07,158
You're innocent.

71
00:06:11,913 --> 00:06:12,997
I ran away

72
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,210
because I really

73
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:21,506
wanted him to die.

74
00:06:24,842 --> 00:06:25,927
Sang-tae knows that.

75
00:06:27,345 --> 00:06:28,346
And

76
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:30,681
so did you.

77
00:06:33,184 --> 00:06:34,811
What do you know about me?

78
00:06:35,311 --> 00:06:37,355
Who are you to act up like this?

79
00:06:38,147 --> 00:06:39,273
Hypocrite.

80
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:43,653
There's no way I'm innocent.

81
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:45,613
So

82
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:47,824
are you going to sacrifice
your entire life

83
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:50,535
for your brother
so you can atone for your sin?

84
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:55,832
Why did you

85
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,376
save me

86
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:02,672
from the river that day?

87
00:07:04,841 --> 00:07:06,175
You should've just left me to die.

88
00:07:08,594 --> 00:07:09,929
If I had died that day,

89
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:14,392
I wouldn't have had to live this way.

90
00:07:48,176 --> 00:07:50,261
I kept calling for him.

91
00:07:51,762 --> 00:07:52,805
But he left.

92
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:56,100
He just abandoned me.

93
00:07:58,269 --> 00:08:00,313
He left me all alone

94
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,691
and left far away.

95
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:05,443
He tried to kill his brother.

96
00:08:06,235 --> 00:08:07,695
I heard he pushed him into a river.

97
00:08:08,779 --> 00:08:10,990
You really can't tell a book by its cover.

98
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:14,118
No wonder his smile

99
00:08:14,202 --> 00:08:16,370
always seemed a bit creepy.

100
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:18,247
I saw it.

101
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:21,292
-What?
-I could tell

102
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:23,419
by the look in his eyes.

103
00:08:23,836 --> 00:08:27,590
He's a guy who's cruel enough
to kill someone.

104
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:29,842
-But he's handsome.
-Ignore her. She's talking gibberish.

105
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:31,093
Yes, he really is.

106
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:32,762
So what if he's handsome?

107
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:36,599
You crazy shaman!

108
00:08:36,682 --> 00:08:38,142
-Jeong-tae!
-Watch what comes out of your mouth!

109
00:08:48,694 --> 00:08:50,238
My gosh.

110
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:00,206
Wipe your face.

111
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:04,877
Mr. Joo Jeong-tae was really good

112
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:07,213
at aiming people with a fire extinguisher.

113
00:09:07,296 --> 00:09:09,799
I guess he really was a firefighter
back in the days.

114
00:09:09,882 --> 00:09:12,009
That stuff is used to put out fire,
not people.

115
00:09:12,093 --> 00:09:13,594
Didn't you hear what he said?

116
00:09:14,136 --> 00:09:16,847
The stuff we said is
what caused this mess.

117
00:09:17,598 --> 00:09:20,768
Let's be careful of what we say
from now on.

118
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:23,646
Let's not even talk about Mr. Moon.

119
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:27,024
My gosh.

120
00:09:29,443 --> 00:09:30,903
-Ms. Park.
-Yes?

121
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:33,864
Here are Ms. Park Ok-ran's recent
counseling records that you asked for.

122
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:38,869
But why are you interested in her
all of a sudden?

123
00:09:40,454 --> 00:09:44,542
Well, she's been experiencing
severe changes in mood lately.

124
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:46,544
And her affect seems
very different from usual.

125
00:09:46,627 --> 00:09:47,587
AFFECT: EXPRESSION OF FEELINGS
AND EMOTION

126
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:50,464
I just want to see
if there's a specific cause to that.

127
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:52,341
COUNSELING ROOM

128
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:57,054
Are you getting along okay
at the hospital?

129
00:09:57,138 --> 00:09:58,889
I have a question.

130
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:02,727
Go ahead.

131
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:05,605
Did he really try to kill him?

132
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:07,898
What?

133
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:10,610
Did the caregiver really try
to kill his brother?

134
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:19,076
No, I believe there was a misunderstanding
between the two.

135
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:28,628
Ms. Park.

136
00:10:30,838 --> 00:10:33,049
Why do you think Othello...

137
00:10:34,508 --> 00:10:35,593
killed his wife?

138
00:10:39,722 --> 00:10:40,973
Because of a misunderstanding.

139
00:10:53,527 --> 00:10:55,029
I brought your bag.

140
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,501
Sang-tae, are you sleeping?

141
00:11:10,252 --> 00:11:11,087
Aren't you hungry?

142
00:11:13,589 --> 00:11:15,216
This place feels really empty, doesn't it?

143
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:18,094
I'll move you to the ward
once there's an empty room.

144
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:20,805
By any chance, if you want to go home--

145
00:11:20,888 --> 00:11:23,265
No. I don't want to go home.

146
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:27,144
Okay, you can stay here for a while.

147
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:31,690
Let me know if you need anything.

148
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:33,734
Okay?

149
00:11:53,045 --> 00:11:55,798
My gosh, he's been out of reach all day.

150
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:57,466
This is driving me crazy.

151
00:11:58,008 --> 00:12:00,386
I bet there's one more person
who's having a mental breakdown.

152
00:12:00,469 --> 00:12:01,470
Do you think I should go?

153
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:03,264
You can't do anything to help Mun-yeong.

154
00:12:03,347 --> 00:12:05,141
No, I was talking about Mr. Moon Sang-tae.

155
00:12:05,641 --> 00:12:06,475
Hey.

156
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:09,145
God knows when she'll start
writing her next book

157
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:11,564
now that she got involved in their fight.

158
00:12:11,647 --> 00:12:13,441
But you're worried about
the older brother?

159
00:12:13,524 --> 00:12:14,358
Unbelievable!

160
00:12:15,651 --> 00:12:17,653
You really care about
nothing else but money.

161
00:12:18,154 --> 00:12:19,155
What did you just say?

162
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:21,824
Your parents gave you an appropriate name.

163
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:24,285
"Sang-in" means merchant!
You're all about the money!

164
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:28,414
Then I guess according to your name,
you're always out of luck.

165
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:32,793
My parents went to a naming center
and paid 300,000 won for my name.

166
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:35,713
My great-grandfather who fought for our
country's independence gave me my name!

167
00:12:36,964 --> 00:12:38,424
Stop it, you guys.

168
00:12:39,008 --> 00:12:42,261
I'm worried sick because I don't even know
if my friend is dead or alive.

169
00:12:42,344 --> 00:12:44,180
But all you care about is selling books.

170
00:12:44,263 --> 00:12:47,349
If Ko Mun-yeong hadn't convinced him
to go on a trip with her,

171
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:48,767
none of this would've happened.

172
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:53,189
It takes two to tango.

173
00:12:53,564 --> 00:12:56,066
He went with her because he wanted to.

174
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:58,652
He left his brother here all by himself

175
00:12:58,736 --> 00:13:00,696
and spent the night with Mun-yeong.

176
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:02,698
I bet he went with her
with an ulterior motive.

177
00:13:06,285 --> 00:13:08,412
I really think you guys should shut up.

178
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:12,333
Ko Mun-yeong is the cause of all this!

179
00:13:13,834 --> 00:13:17,087
Moon Gang-tae is the cunning one!

180
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:19,048
-Are you serious?
-Seriously?

181
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:21,175
-Are you kidding me?
-Look who's talking.

182
00:13:21,258 --> 00:13:23,052
Oh, gosh. Did you work out?

183
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:29,433
Let's eat.

184
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:31,602
-Okay.
-Okay.

185
00:13:49,411 --> 00:13:51,372
I know they have a lot on their minds.

186
00:13:52,164 --> 00:13:54,542
But I hope they didn't skip their meals.

187
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:25,489
UNDER SEDATION
DO NOT DISTURB

188
00:14:49,847 --> 00:14:50,890
Sang-tae.

189
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:04,403
Why did you save me
from the river that day?

190
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:06,280
You should've just left me to die.

191
00:15:06,363 --> 00:15:07,573
That horrible jerk.

192
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:39,063
Why is he just sitting there
instead of going inside?

193
00:15:44,276 --> 00:15:48,113
When someone has autism,
it means they shut the door to the world.

194
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:50,866
Gang-tae is

195
00:15:52,326 --> 00:15:55,329
waiting for Sang-tae
to open that door first.

196
00:16:20,854 --> 00:16:22,815
He's like a trapped ghost.

197
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,819
He can't approach you.

198
00:16:27,945 --> 00:16:29,279
But he can't leave either.

199
00:16:30,447 --> 00:16:32,282
He's just like a ghost that's trapped.

200
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:39,248
I bet it's really hot in there.

201
00:16:40,332 --> 00:16:42,042
It's driving you crazy, isn't it?

202
00:16:44,753 --> 00:16:45,796
Wait a minute.

203
00:16:46,588 --> 00:16:50,050
How long did it take
for Crown Prince Sado to die

204
00:16:50,134 --> 00:16:51,969
in the rice chest?

205
00:16:55,097 --> 00:16:56,682
I can't remember if he died

206
00:16:57,891 --> 00:16:59,393
due to hunger

207
00:17:02,104 --> 00:17:04,064
or died due to the heat.

208
00:17:06,358 --> 00:17:08,902
You brothers are both

209
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:10,696
extremely stubborn.

210
00:17:11,947 --> 00:17:14,116
I'll take your brother upstairs.

211
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,994
So come out of there
and get some fresh air.

212
00:17:17,077 --> 00:17:19,079
And go to the bathroom.

213
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:20,497
My goodness.

214
00:17:58,035 --> 00:17:59,078
Eat this.

215
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:02,122
This is the best
when you don't have an appetite.

216
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:09,004
Have you tried a three-legged race?

217
00:18:09,588 --> 00:18:13,050
You know, where each pair have their
adjacent legs bound together and run.

218
00:18:16,053 --> 00:18:18,472
I tried it a couple of times
at my son's school sports event.

219
00:18:18,639 --> 00:18:20,557
But I always ended up falling down first.

220
00:18:21,141 --> 00:18:23,310
So we never got to reach the finish line.

221
00:18:26,563 --> 00:18:28,982
It's like you and your brother
are running a three-legged race.

222
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:35,322
Do you think

223
00:18:37,157 --> 00:18:39,618
we're both holding each other back?

224
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:41,245
No.

225
00:18:42,746 --> 00:18:44,164
You're both relying on each other.

226
00:18:44,748 --> 00:18:47,709
As long as one person stays strong
when the other person falls down,

227
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:49,753
you guys will never fall down together.

228
00:18:50,879 --> 00:18:52,214
Try your best to stay strong.

229
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:54,216
Who knows?

230
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:57,302
Sang-tae might be the one
to help you one day.

231
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:09,690
I thought Sang-tae

232
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:15,654
had forgotten about everything.

233
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:20,159
He never once mentioned that day.

234
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:26,206
So I thought he had erased it
from his mind.

235
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:28,250
That's what you wanted to believe.

236
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:33,755
But most people with autism
have really good memory.

237
00:19:34,423 --> 00:19:38,051
They either just try to avoid
their emotions

238
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:42,598
or express their emotions
a little differently compared to us.

239
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:46,351
"Avoid"?

240
00:19:46,768 --> 00:19:48,604
You shouldn't avoid it.
Just face it head-on.

241
00:19:51,106 --> 00:19:52,357
Come back to work.

242
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:54,902
Ms. Lee A-reum's ex-husband told me

243
00:19:54,985 --> 00:19:58,739
he's going to drop all charges
after I blackmailed him a little.

244
00:19:59,364 --> 00:20:01,491
I suspended you for a few days,

245
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:02,910
so that's more than enough.

246
00:20:05,621 --> 00:20:07,873
-Is that really--
-I need you back because the guy

247
00:20:07,956 --> 00:20:10,459
who's doing your job is terrible at it.
Maybe I should fire him.

248
00:20:15,505 --> 00:20:16,506
That hurts!

249
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:18,133
Ms. Park! Ms. Nam!

250
00:20:19,259 --> 00:20:22,346
Hey, stop. Jeong-tae.
You shouldn't bite people.

251
00:20:22,971 --> 00:20:24,223
You're not a dog or a crocodile.

252
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:26,183
-My gosh, please stop.
-That's enough.

253
00:20:26,266 --> 00:20:28,352
It really hurts! Let me go!

254
00:20:28,852 --> 00:20:29,811
Mr. Moon.

255
00:20:35,692 --> 00:20:36,526
Gang-tae.

256
00:20:38,362 --> 00:20:39,279
Gang-tae.

257
00:20:41,573 --> 00:20:43,742
He refused to take his medicine.

258
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:45,827
He's a patient.
He should take his medicine.

259
00:20:46,578 --> 00:20:48,413
You can't force patients
to take their medicine.

260
00:20:48,997 --> 00:20:50,999
He did it on purpose.

261
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:54,127
He lured my fingers near his mouth
so he could bite them.

262
00:20:55,212 --> 00:20:57,130
-Why would he do that?
-I don't know.

263
00:20:57,214 --> 00:20:58,131
