799
01:12:36,060 --> 01:12:37,603
so I chose this in a heartbeat.

800
01:12:37,686 --> 01:12:39,396
Our hearts put together.

801
01:12:39,480 --> 01:12:41,273
It's perfect for us, isn't it?

802
01:12:41,357 --> 01:12:43,525
You write books, and I sell them.

803
01:12:53,452 --> 01:12:55,662
My gosh, it suits you perfectly.

804
01:12:55,746 --> 01:12:58,707
Oh, my.
You're dazzlingly beautiful, Mun-yeong.

805
01:12:58,791 --> 01:13:01,627
This is your way of pushing me
to get moving on my next book, isn't it?

806
01:13:01,710 --> 01:13:04,671
Okay, point taken.
I should get moving if you're pushing.

807
01:13:04,755 --> 01:13:06,256
Hey, what are you talking about?

808
01:13:11,303 --> 01:13:12,388
Mun-yeong.

809
01:13:15,849 --> 01:13:16,892
Hey, why are you--

810
01:13:16,975 --> 01:13:17,935
Stay there.

811
01:13:22,940 --> 01:13:25,734
Sang-tae, Moon Sang-tae! Open up, bestie.

812
01:13:25,818 --> 01:13:27,611
It's me. Open the door.

813
01:13:32,658 --> 01:13:34,785
No, no, I can't...

814
01:13:34,868 --> 01:13:37,162
If you don't let me in,
I'll break down the door.

815
01:13:39,248 --> 01:13:42,668
No, don't.
Don't break the door. Don't do that.

816
01:13:42,751 --> 01:13:45,629
I should... I should call the police.
What was the number?

817
01:13:45,712 --> 01:13:48,048
I brought a power saw. I'm not kidding.

818
01:13:48,924 --> 01:13:52,428
Gosh. Dial 911 to report a fire.

819
01:13:52,511 --> 01:13:53,929
Dial 111 to report a spy.

820
01:13:54,012 --> 01:13:56,765
-To report a crime...
-I can only wait three seconds.

821
01:13:56,849 --> 01:13:58,225
You'd better open up before that.

822
01:13:58,308 --> 01:13:59,560
-One.
-No...

823
01:13:59,643 --> 01:14:00,727
Two.

824
01:14:01,979 --> 01:14:03,897
-Three!
-Don't break it!

825
01:14:03,981 --> 01:14:05,399
Don't break down the door.

826
01:14:21,331 --> 01:14:23,250
-Here.
-Oh, Mang-tae.

827
01:14:24,793 --> 01:14:26,128
Take it back.

828
01:14:26,378 --> 01:14:27,254
I'm giving him up.

829
01:14:27,838 --> 01:14:28,672
You're giving him up?

830
01:14:29,756 --> 01:14:31,300
Instead of Mang-tae,

831
01:14:31,758 --> 01:14:32,593
can I have Sang-tae?

832
01:14:34,052 --> 01:14:35,804
I want Sang-tae.

833
01:14:41,518 --> 01:14:42,769
That smile is fake.

834
01:14:42,853 --> 01:14:45,898
No, it's real.
I'm bored without you, bestie.

835
01:14:47,733 --> 01:14:48,650
You're lying.

836
01:14:48,734 --> 01:14:50,235
I came to pick you up.

837
01:14:50,319 --> 01:14:51,570
You're lying.

838
01:14:52,154 --> 01:14:53,197
To tell you the truth,

839
01:14:54,448 --> 01:14:55,407
it's my birthday today--

840
01:14:55,491 --> 01:14:57,034
You're lying. You're lying to me.

841
01:14:57,117 --> 01:14:59,286
I want you to hang out with me,
as a birthday present.

842
01:14:59,369 --> 01:15:00,621
You're lying.

843
01:15:00,704 --> 01:15:02,623
Are you a lie detector or what?

844
01:15:02,706 --> 01:15:04,249
You're lying. Stop lying to me!

845
01:15:04,333 --> 01:15:06,460
You're lying!

846
01:15:06,543 --> 01:15:09,421
Liars are bad. Only bad people lie.

847
01:15:09,630 --> 01:15:12,341
Liar. She told me
she was going out by herself.

848
01:15:12,424 --> 01:15:13,467
All by herself.

849
01:15:13,550 --> 01:15:15,677
Besties don't keep secrets
from each other,

850
01:15:15,761 --> 01:15:18,013
but those two went somewhere fun
without me.

851
01:15:18,096 --> 01:15:20,098
I don't need this.

852
01:15:20,182 --> 01:15:21,558
I don't need a camping car anymore.

853
01:15:21,642 --> 01:15:24,478
I don't need a camping car.
I don't need this anymore!

854
01:15:24,686 --> 01:15:25,521
I don't need it!

855
01:15:55,050 --> 01:15:56,218
Sang-tae.

856
01:15:58,095 --> 01:15:59,930
The one who's really bad

857
01:16:01,431 --> 01:16:04,226
is the person who doesn't believe
anything others say.

858
01:16:04,977 --> 01:16:06,937
No, you're wrong. No.

859
01:16:08,313 --> 01:16:10,482
You know the story,
The Boy Who Cried Wolf, right?

860
01:16:11,858 --> 01:16:13,527
You don't look okay.

861
01:16:13,610 --> 01:16:15,904
Why don't you get an IV drip
instead of taking medicine?

862
01:16:16,071 --> 01:16:16,989
No, it's okay.

863
01:16:19,700 --> 01:16:20,617
This is enough.

864
01:16:20,701 --> 01:16:23,870
The shepherd boy lied all the time.

865
01:16:26,123 --> 01:16:29,918
The boy repeatedly lied to the villagers

866
01:16:30,419 --> 01:16:32,838
that a real wolf showed up.

867
01:16:35,716 --> 01:16:38,302
Do you know why the boy
tricked the villagers like that?

868
01:16:40,304 --> 01:16:42,556
Because he was bored, obviously.

869
01:16:43,056 --> 01:16:43,890
Wrong.

870
01:16:46,184 --> 01:16:47,352
Because he was lonely.

871
01:16:51,440 --> 01:16:54,860
He did that because he was so lonely,
all by himself in the mountains.

872
01:17:58,799 --> 01:18:01,551
-What happened?
-Ms. Park Ok-ran smacked him in the head.

873
01:18:01,635 --> 01:18:03,345
-What?
-Well...

874
01:18:03,929 --> 01:18:05,472
She said she dropped something important

875
01:18:05,555 --> 01:18:08,266
in the garden earlier
and asked me to help her find it,

876
01:18:08,350 --> 01:18:09,810
so I stepped out with her and--

877
01:18:09,893 --> 01:18:12,104
She suddenly grabbed a stone
and hit him in the head.

878
01:18:13,689 --> 01:18:15,440
He passed out and woke up just now.

879
01:18:17,150 --> 01:18:19,486
What about Ms. Park Ok-ran?
Where is she now?

880
01:18:19,569 --> 01:18:22,572
What do we do? It looks like she escaped.

881
01:18:22,656 --> 01:18:24,574
Call the police station nearby. Hurry.

882
01:18:24,658 --> 01:18:25,742
-Come with me.
-Okay.

883
01:18:26,868 --> 01:18:28,995
Anything else? Did she say anything else?

884
01:18:29,746 --> 01:18:31,581
She said today is
a very important day for her.

885
01:18:32,207 --> 01:18:34,876
I heard her mumbling about
having to meet someone today.

886
01:18:34,960 --> 01:18:36,586
Today is a very important day to me.

887
01:18:37,337 --> 01:18:38,839
-What if
-Did you get through?

888
01:18:38,922 --> 01:18:41,341
the writer Do Hui-jae actually isn't dead?

889
01:18:41,550 --> 01:18:43,218
-What if she just disappeared?
-Mr. Moon!

890
01:18:43,301 --> 01:18:45,095
-Then we know one thing for sure.
-No.

891
01:18:45,178 --> 01:18:46,805
-She'll definitely come back
-No.

892
01:18:46,888 --> 01:18:48,974
to see her husband and daughter.

893
01:18:49,057 --> 01:18:50,142
No!

894
01:18:55,147 --> 01:18:56,857
The shepherd boy

895
01:18:57,941 --> 01:18:59,943
lied because he was so lonely.

896
01:19:02,195 --> 01:19:04,740
But when a wolf actually appeared,

897
01:19:05,574 --> 01:19:07,784
no one came to help him.

898
01:19:10,495 --> 01:19:11,913
Had even just one person

899
01:19:13,749 --> 01:19:16,293
believed him and came to help him,

900
01:19:17,502 --> 01:19:19,588
the boy wouldn't have died.

901
01:19:49,326 --> 01:19:50,202
Ko Mun-yeong.

902
01:19:52,788 --> 01:19:53,830
Mun-yeong.

903
01:20:50,262 --> 01:20:51,346
I think...

904
01:20:52,180 --> 01:20:54,724
I'm finally living a normal life.

905
01:20:56,601 --> 01:20:58,562
You're an adult, right?

906
01:20:58,645 --> 01:21:01,690
An adult like Ko Gil-dong,
who can accept others as a family.

907
01:21:01,773 --> 01:21:04,150
-Gang-tae is mine.
-Gang-tae belongs to Gang-tae

908
01:21:04,234 --> 01:21:06,695
You can't have Gang-tae! Never!

909
01:21:06,778 --> 01:21:09,239
She had multiple plastic surgeries.

910
01:21:09,322 --> 01:21:10,740
She's been acting weird.

911
01:21:12,951 --> 01:21:15,537
I want a big brother like you!

912
01:21:17,956 --> 01:21:18,832
Gang-tae is...

913
01:21:19,332 --> 01:21:20,750
Happy.

914
01:21:21,334 --> 01:21:23,128
Gang-tae is happy.

